    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently `treesitter` uses the `runtimepath` order for determining which query files get used. This creates a problem since,\n\n1. Plugin manager's by design need to modify the `runtimepath`.\n2. Lazy loading can change when/where a new path gets added to the `runtimepath`.\n\nFor example, [this issue](https://github.com/OXY2DEV/markview.nvim/issues/332#issuecomment-3328643565) has been plaguing me for months and I don't know how to fix this without messing with the user's `runtimepath`(which may be an unexpected behaviour).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAllow some way to specify which directory to use for the queries for a specific tree-sitter parser.\n\n> This could be used in the `presentation mode` in the future to quickly change the appearance of the buffer text without needing to implement them for each file type. So, I think this is could be a good feature to add to Neovim.",
